candidates = ['', '', '','','','','']
accurancy = [accurancy1,accurancy2,accurancy3,accurancy4,accurancy5,accurancy6,accurancy7]
error_rate = [error_rate1,error_rate2,error_rate3,error_rate4,error_rate5,error_rate6,error_rate7]
x = np.arange(len(candidates))
width = 0.3
plt.bar(x, accurancy, width, color='green', label='')
plt.bar(x + width, error_rate, width, color='blue', label='')
plt.xticks(x + width / 2, candidates)
plt.ylabel('%')
plt.title('')
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1,1), loc='upper left')
plt.show()
In [40]:
candidates = ['', '', '','','','','']
accurancy = [accurancy1,accurancy2,accurancy3,accurancy4,accurancy5,accurancy6,accurancy7]
error_rate = [error_rate1,error_rate2,error_rate3,error_rate4,error_rate5,error_rate6,error_rate7]
x = np.arange(len(candidates))
plt.bar(x, accurancy, color='blue', label='')
plt.bar(x, error_rate, color='green', label='', bottom=error_rate)
plt.xticks(x, candidates)
plt.xlabel('')
plt.ylabel('%')
plt.title('')
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1,1), loc='upper left')
plt.show()

labels = ['','','' ]    # 
size = [sum(data1['result']==''),
        sum(data1['result']==''),
        sum(data1['result']=='')]
        
        # 

plt.pie(size,                           # 
        labels = labels,                # 
        autopct = "%1.1f%%",            # 
        #explode = separeted,            # 
        pctdistance = 0.6,              # 
        textprops = {"fontsize" : 12},  # 
        shadow=True)                    # 

plt.axis('equal')                                          # 
plt.title("", {"fontsize" : 18})  # 
plt.legend(loc = "best")                                   #  

plt.savefig(".jpg",   # 
            bbox_inches='tight',      # 
            pad_inches=0.0)           # 
plt.show()
